Altitude Linux native BDB boot database.

The init process copies this seed database to /var/bdb during early boot.
Runtime mutations use the C engine's fsync-backed redo WAL. Run `bdb check`
to validate table structure, types and primary-key uniqueness.
`bdb transact TABLE=DATA.bdb ...` publishes validated table images atomically.
`bdbconf` uses it to apply the versioned `/etc/minibash/system.conf` manifest.
